  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most jurisdictions around the world. It is typically covered under:\n\n1. Criminal legislation\n2. Anti-money laundering (AML) laws\n3. Financial crime statutes\n\nMoney laundering involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. Most countries have specific laws and severe penalties for money laundering, which can include:\n\n- Significant fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n\nThe specific legal framework and penalties vary by country, but money laundering is universally treated as a serious criminal activity.",
